Subject: Re: [T2] More Spark Plug Tightening Info

Josh, you really never noticed that before....
 
Pretty much all plug
manufacturers do spec usually somewhere between 1/4 (more commonly in my
experience) - 2/3 turn past contact for metal gasket, 1/16 turn past contact
for tapered seat in their instructions.  Some go so far as to mention you can
use the 1/16 past contact when re-installing a crushed metal gasket plug. 
I've known pros who have done it according to something like that for years. 
Again I still feel it is mostly aggresious overtightening that causes issue,
and this would not constitute same.  But like anything done in such a manner
establishing "clean contact" to start your turn is open to a bit of debate,
probably one that the anti-antiseize croud will bemoan.  The 1/16 turn for
tapered seat gives one an insight into how fast torque and clamping pressure
build.
 
I do find the French made NGK plugs pretty curious...
 
John
 
 
