I had never noticed this before.
It looks to say once the plug
is fully seated
(by hand I assume), tighten another 1/2 to 2/3 turns if the
plug has a crush
washer.
If the plug is designed without a washer, then only
tighten another
1/16 turn.

I know VW has a torque spec for plugs, but after
reading a lot of
articles and discussions here (e.g. anti-seize discussion) it
seems that these
recommendations from the NGK packaging should be fine.
